Key Match Events: Schwarber and Weston Wilson each drove in two runs
Philadelphia Phillies avoided a series sweep and closed out the regular season with a 6-3 win over the Washington Nationals
Phillies reliever José Ruiz sealed the game with a strikeout and a catch
Post-Match Reflections: Philadelphia manager Rob Thomson was happy with the way the team finished the season
Washington manager Dave Martinez acknowledged the team's effort and highlighted the improvement of young players
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillies finished with a 95-67 record, the second-best in the National League
The Nationals went 71-91 for the second straight season
Philadelphia had a bye in the first round of the playoffs
The Phillies will face either the Milwaukee Brewers or the NL’s third wild card in a division series starting Saturday in Philadelphia
Others: Zack Wheeler ended his regular season with 200 innings pitched
Luis García Jr. homered in the first inning for Washington
Nick Castellanos became the first member of the Phillies to play in 162 games in a season since Freddy Galvis in 2017
